      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCO BOOM (1) has a strong record here with two wins and three placings from six starts. Missed the frame latest (29.87) when fourth over 520m at Nowra in a Grade 5. Appeals as a leading chance in this. SPRING WITNESS (2) turned in a plain effort last time when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Best Surprise (30.12) in a Grade 4/5. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Cannot be taken lightly. DASHING FOR GOLD (7) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when seventh (30.63), beaten 7 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Key runner on best form. RELEASE POINT (4) is another with top-three prospects.",
